            <section>
               <title value="Hospital course note"/>
               <code>
                  <coding>
                     <system value="http://loinc.org"/>
                     <code value="8648-8"/>
                     <display value="Hospital course note"/>
                  </coding>
               </code>
               <text>
                  <status value="generated"/>
                  <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you regarding your patient, a 58-year-old female who was admitted on 11/12/2001 at her own request for elective surgical sterilization. Pre-operative assessment confirmed she was a suitable candidate for the procedure, with no contraindications identified. Routine pre-operative investigations including blood work and anaesthetic assessment were within acceptable parameters. On 12/12/2001, the patient underwent bilateral tubal ligation under general anaesthesia without intraoperative complications. Post-operative recovery was uneventful, and the patient was discharged home in good condition the same day. She has been counselled regarding the permanent and irreversible nature of the procedure. No further gynaecological follow-up is required from our side. Please arrange routine post-operative review in your practice. Should any concerns arise, do not hesitate to contact our department.</div>
               </text>
            </section>
